@koutoftimer thanks for the report! Could it be that any of the middleware classes you use have the `@staticmethod` decorator on `process_request` or `process_response`?

If that's the case and there are no pressing reasons for those methods to be static, I suggest to remove that decorator and make the methods "normal" instance methods (this is the interface suggested by Django).

If that's not an option, you can disable our instrumentation of middlewares by updating the `OPBEAT` configuration dictionary like this:

    OPBEAT = {
        # other settings
        'INSTRUMENT_DJANGO_MIDDLEWARE': False,
    }

By disabling instrumentation of middleware, we lose insight into code paths where the response is generated by a middleware and not a view. One example is Django's `CommonMiddleware`, which creates `HttpResponseRedirect` responses due to the `APPEND_SLASH` setting (https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.8/ref/middleware/#module-django.middleware.common). The rest of the Performance insights are unaffected by this setting. 

We're looking into detecting this case automatically in the future.

